The paper discusses abstract state machines (ASMs) which are a formal method for specifying and verifying algorithms. This makes it likely that the paper would belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses sequential, parallel, and distributed ASMs, which suggests that it could also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses evolving algebras, which could also make it relevant to the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category.
